The paper deals with accountability and security properties in computer systems, which are typically studied in the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a formal study of program actions, which falls under the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper uses techniques such as soundness and cause analysis, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with protocols and their prescribed programs, which are studied in the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
